      "description": "One-loop five-point pentagon relevant for $gg \\to t\\bar{t}H$ production, with all five internal top-quark propagators of mass $m_t$ and external on-shell conditions $p_1^2=p_2^2=0$, $p_3^2=p_4^2=m_t^2$, $p_5^2=m_H^2$. Identified as Topology C of Ref. Buccioni:2023okz. The family has 29 master integrals, evaluated numerically at the phase-space point $s_0=\\{1, 1823191/3567300, 751/23, -155/11, 85/12, 12271/759, -59689/3300\\}$ to $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^{10})$ via the dimension-changing transformation applied to auxiliary-mass differential equations solved with 18 regular and 2 singular series-expansion points. Validated against AMFlow; precision of the top-sector integral reported in Tab. I.",
